<Layout title="Software Engineering Fundamentals.">
	<main> 
  <h1>Software Engineering Fundamentals</h1>
    <p>
        Ah, <span class="italic">software engineering</span> – that mystical realm where we, the chosen ones, wield the power of React, React Native, TypeScript, and JavaScript to bend reality to our will. It's not just a job, it's an <span class="bold">art form</span>, a science, and let's be honest, a <span class="bold">superpower</span>.
    </p>
    <p>
        First off, let's talk about the basics: <span class="bold">coding</span>. Now, I know everyone says it's all about writing clean, maintainable code. But come on, real geniuses don’t need comments or documentation. Our code is self-explanatory, a masterpiece of digital craftsmanship. If someone can’t understand it, well, maybe they're just not cut out for this world.
    </p>
    <p>
        Then there's <span class="italic">debugging</span>. Some say it’s where you learn the most. I say it's a pesky step that just slows down my brilliance. Why spend hours fixing bugs when you can just rewrite everything in a more complicated way? After all, if there are no bugs you can find, do they even exist?
    </p>
    <p>
        Version control? Sure, it's essential. But let's be real, it's mostly there to prove how my code was perfect before everyone else messed it up. And when it comes to merging branches, it's a battle, and only the fittest code survives.
    </p>
    <p>
        Now, let’s talk about <span class="bold">teamwork</span>. Collaboration is for those who can't handle the pressure of genius. Pair programming? More like slowing-me-down programming. I work best as a lone wolf, a solitary genius fighting against the mediocrity of groupthink.
    </p>
    <p>
        And deadlines – oh, the mortal enemy of creativity. Why constrain innovation within the arbitrary bounds of time? True art takes time, and my code is nothing less than a digital Mona Lisa.
    </p>
    <p>
        In conclusion, software engineering is not just about building applications. It's about proving that you're the smartest person in the room. It's not just a career; it's a lifestyle. A lifestyle that says, "I am the code, and the code is me." And as for life's perils – what perils? In the digital realm, I am <span class="italic">invincible</span>.
    </p>
  </main>
</Layout>

<style>
	main {
		margin: auto;
		padding: 1rem;
		width: 800px;
		max-width: calc(100% - 2rem);
		color: white;
		font-size: 20px;
		line-height: 1.6;
	}
	h1 {
		font-size: 4rem;
		font-weight: 700;
		line-height: 1;
		text-align: center;
		margin-bottom: 1em;
	}
  .bold { font-weight: bold; color: red; }
  .italic { font-style: italic; color: yellow; }
</style>
